cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the optimization of read-optimized databases, which are commonly used in data warehousing and analytics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses algorithms and optimizations for handling large amounts of data, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of multi-core CPUs, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
